<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANIEL CALDER; UCLA ENGLISH PROFESSOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Daniel G. Calder, 55, professor of English at UCLA, noted scholar of Old 
English literature and a leader in the development of gay and lesbian studies 
on the UCLA campus. Editor and translator of several works on Old English 
literature -- "Old English Poetry: Essays on Style," "Cynewulf," "A New 
Critical History of Old English Literature" among them -- Calder had been 
working on a book of contemporary gay fiction at his death.He had taught at the 
University of Washington after receiving his doctorate from Indiana University 
in 1969. He joined the UCLA faculty in 1971 and was chairman of the English 
department from 1983 to 1990, a period of great growth in the department's 
stature. Calder also served as associate dean of the School of Theater, Film 
and Television and as acting dean of the division of humanities in UCLA's 
College of Letters and Sciences. In Los Angeles on Aug. 2 of the complications 
of AIDS. 
</P>
