<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; TEAM DRAWS A CROWD IN DENVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Sunday, when the Dodgers played before a crowd of 70,372 at Mile High 
Stadium, it was the largest crowd they had played before in the regular season 
since opening night at the L.A. Coliseum, April 18, 1958, when they played 
before 78,762. 
</P>
<P>
 The crowd Sunday put the Rockies over three million in attendance after only 
52 dates, breaking the record they set last season when they reached the mark 
in 53 dates. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Rafael Bournigal had a scare Monday morning when he couldn't find his 
eyeglasses. He had already packed his suitcase for Cincinnati and sent it down 
to be loaded on the truck to the airport, when he realized he might have packed 
both pairs of the glasses he wears when he plays. The suitcase, though, wasn't 
gone, so he retrieved them. "Can you believe it?" he said. "I wouldn't have 
been able to play today." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Ramon Martinez's wife, Doris, gave birth to a 7-pound, 7-ounce baby girl named 
Doranni on Monday in Los Angeles. Martinez, who went home on Sunday to be with 
his wife, will join the team today in Cincinnati. Martinez is scheduled to 
pitch Thursday against Jose Rijo. MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080994-0044 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 068201 </DOCID>
