PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NFL; KELLY LEADS BILLS TO VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was an easy night for veteran Jim Kelly and a rough night for rookie Heath 
Shuler. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelly, who had been bothered by tendinitis in his throwing shoulder, completed 
nine of 12 passes, including his first seven, as the Buffalo Bills went on to 
beat the Washington Redskins, 13-11, at Orchard Park, N.Y. 
</P>
<P>
 Shuler, the No. 3 pick in this year's draft, did not practice with the 
Redskins until Wednesday because of a contract holdout.Playing the second 
quarter, he completed four of 10 passes for 47 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Vlasic, whose only preseason pass was intercepted, was among five players 
waived by the Tampa Bay Buccaneers. . . . Indianapolis Coach Ted Marchibroda 
said that rookie linebacker Trev Alberts will not require surgery on his 
dislocated right elbow. Alberts will be in a cast 10 days and is expected to be 
out four weeks. . . . Dolphin right tackle Ron Heller has been accused of 
slapping a security worker before Miami's game with Pittsburgh on Saturday. 
Heller denies hitting Edwin Mendez in a dispute over a parking space in the 
players' lot at Joe Robbie Stadium. 
</P>
