<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; FIREFIGHTERS DOUSE BLAZE NEAR LANDFILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters on Monday extinguished a 20-acre fire that burned through thick 
vegetation near the Simi Valley landfill, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The brush fire began about 1 p.m. in rugged terrain off Madera Road, about a 
half-mile north of the Simi Valley Freeway.  
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters from 10 engine companies and several hand crews worked to contain 
the blaze, assisted by a helicopter equipped with a bucket for water drops. The 
fire was contained by 5 p.m., said Nina Raya, spokeswoman for the Ventura 
County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause is still under investigation. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
