<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: NORWALK; ARSENAL SEIZED 
AFTER MAN ALLEGEDLY SHOOTS AT WIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who barricaded himself inside his garage with an arsenal of weapons 
after allegedly shooting at his wife was in custody Monday after surrendering 
to deputies, a sheriff's spokeswoman said.  
</P>
<P>
 John Delgado, 44, was booked on suspicion of spousal abuse and assault with a 
deadly weapon and was held on $500,000 bail, said sheriff's spokeswoman Angie 
McLaughlin. 
</P>
<P>
 Delgado's wife, who was not wounded, had called deputies to the couple's home 
on Lefloss Avenue after the pair argued about 9:30 p.m. Sunday, McLaughlin 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "(The man) had been drinking," McLaughlin said. "Delgado struck her, then 
fired one round at her from a handgun, missing her." Delgado then ran to the 
garage and barricaded himself inside, "stating he was going to kill himself," 
McLaughlin said.  
</P>
<P>
 In the garage was an assortment of 19 weapons, including handguns, shotguns, 
rifles and a large amount of ammunition, McLaughlin said.  
</P>
<P>
 Deputies evacuated several nearby homes and called for a sheriff's special 
weapons team about 11 p.m., but before the team's members arrived, Delgado 
surrendered, McLaughlin said.  
</P>
<P>
 The woman, whose name was not released, suffered only superficial injuries 
when her husband hit her and did not require medical treatment, McLaughlin 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
