<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; LITTLE LEAGUE ALL-STARS GO FOR THE 
STATE TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks Little League all-star team of 9- and 10-year-olds could 
become state champions tonight if they win a baseball game against a team of 
all-stars from Lakewood. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks is undefeated in this section of the tournament and will have 
two chances to win the state championship, said manager Daniel Catalano. 
</P>
<P>
 Even if they lose tonight, the Thousand Oaks team will again play Lakewood -- 
which already has a loss in this section of play -- on Thursday, Catalano said. 
Thousand Oaks beat Lakewood, 6-4, last Tuesday, Catalano said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We definitely have an advantage not having a loss," Catalano said Monday. 
"But Lakewood's a real good team, and the boys are going to have to play a real 
good defense and play their best game." 
</P>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks 13-year-old all-stars are already knocking on the door of 
the Little League World Series, standing just two wins away from a series slot 
after defeating a team from Pearl City, Hawaii, 4-1, in San Jose on Sunday. 
MACK REED 
</P>
