<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; PAROLEE ARRESTED IN ALLEGED RAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By wJULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 39-year-old parolee has been arrested on suspicion of raping a woman at 
knifepoint in his Thousand Oaks motel room, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Nathaniel Pringle was taken into custody Sunday evening after a 20-year-old 
woman told deputies Pringle pulled her into his room at the Econolodge on 
Thousand Oaks Boulevard and assaulted her repeatedly. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman said Pringle, who was on parole after being convicted of burglary in 
Los Angeles County, let her leave about an hour later.  
</P>
<P>
 She then called the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 When deputies arrived at the motel, they found Pringle in his room and 
arrested him, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Detective Darrell Erickson said the case is still under 
investigation and deputies plan to re-interview the woman Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Pringle was being held without bail Monday in the Ventura County Jail. He was 
also arrested for violating his parole in a separate incident in Los Angeles 
County, authorities said. wJULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
