<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: ENCINO; VENTURA BLVD. PLAN WILL BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY HWANGBO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Encino residents are invited to comment at a community meeting tonight on a 
conceptual plan for landscaping Encino's section of Ventura Boulevard.  
</P>
<P>
 Community leaders and architects developed the plan, which they call more than 
a beautification project.It organizes the community into three areas: a town 
center, an employment center and a pedestrian-oriented commercial zone.  
</P>
<P>
 Public comment will also be sought on the location of public parking 
structures and possible routes for a community shuttle. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposal calls for creating a town center at Balboa and Ventura boulevards 
and consolidating and increasing park land in the area.  
</P>
<P>
 Tall palms and banners would be added to areas with one- and two-story 
buildings. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting, sponsored by the Los Angeles City Planning Department and the 
Ventura Boulevard Specific Plan Review Board, will be held at 7 p.m. in the 
auditorium of the Encino Community Center, 4935 Balboa Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The event, which will display drawings by architects and landscape architects, 
is the first of two in Encino.  
</P>
<P>
 The designers will incorporate public comment from the meeting into the plan 
and present the revised proposal for public review at the second meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Other communities along Ventura Boulevard, from Woodland Hills to Studio City, 
have held or will hold public meetings to introduce conceptual plans for their 
areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The final plans for all the communities will be submitted by the Plan Review 
Board to the Planning Department as recommendations at the end of the year. KAY 
HWANGBO 
</P>
</TEXT>
