<HEADLINE>
<P>
AVENUE CLEANUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 As west Ventura taxpayers and registered voters, we would like to see the 
rebuilding, revitalization, rejuvenation and cleanup of Ventura Avenue.  
</P>
<P>
 Given many years of deterioration and neglect and with the avenue's history as 
the economic heart of our great city, reinvesting in our community is the least 
we can expect.Even with today's constraints on public revenues, we are 
convinced that the benefits of this investment in Ventura Avenue's 
infrastructure far outweigh any fiscal concerns. 
</P>
<P>
 We invite all Venturans to volunteer their time, labor, economic resources 
and, most of all, their moral and vocal support for the renewal of the avenue. 
We would like to start the renewal by asking our Ventura City Council and city 
officials to approve and fund the repair of the crumbling sidewalks along 
Ventura Avenue and construction of curbs and sidewalks where they have never 
existed. 
</P>
<P>
 We also extend an open invitation to our business community, schools, 
churches, clubs, societies, associations, agencies and many other organizations 
to contribute and join us in the renewal, revitalization and cleanup of Ventura 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 JESUS CAMILO 
</P>
<P>
 PHILIP REED 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 
</P>
<P>
 Jesus Camilo and Philip Reed are co-chairmen of the revitalization 
subcommittee of the West Ventura Action Committee . 
</P>
</TEXT>
