<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PREMIERE RADIO REBOUNDS WITH SOLID PROFIT BOOST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Premiere Radio Networks Inc., a Sherman Oaks company that produces and 
distributes syndicated radio programming, reported profit turnarounds in the 
second quarter and first half compared to year-earlier losses. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended June 30, Premiere earned $383,236, in contrast 
with a loss of $43,185 in the second quarter of 1993.Its quarterly revenue 
jumped 66%, to $4.27 million from $2.58 million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, the company had net income of $1.37 million, while its 
revenue soared 71%, to $7.79 million. In the first half of 1993, Premiere had a 
loss of $325,843 on $4.55 million in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Premiere attributed the financial rebound to its acquisition strategy, which 
depressed 1993 results but contributed to earnings this year. Among those 
acquisitions were nine radio programs purchased last year from Olympia Networks 
of Missouri Inc. and an investment in Mediabase Research Corp., which Premiere 
now owns. 
</P>
