<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: LESLIE'S POOLMART EARNINGS RISE IN QUARTER, 1ST HALF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Leslie's Poolmart, a Chatsworth-based swimming pool supplies retailer, 
reported higher earnings in the second quarter and first half of the year.The 
results were driven by its growth plan, increased same-store sales and its 
everyday low-price strategy, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the quarter ended June 30, Leslie's had a profit of $7.28 million, up 21% 
from net income of $6.01 million a year ago. Its sales totaled $65.4 million, a 
19% gain from $54.9 million in sales in the second quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, Leslie's earnings jumped 56%, to $3.72 million, while 
sales grew 18%, to $78.7 million. A year earlier, Leslie's earned $2.38 million 
on $66.6 million in sales. 
</P>
