REGIONAL EARNINGS: DOLCO'S PROFIT UP 7% IN SECOND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dolco Packaging Corp., a Sherman Oaks manufacturer of plastic packaging 
products, reported a second-quarter profit of $959,000, up 7% from its 
year-earlier net income of $900,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's sales for the three months ended June 30 totaled $15.4 million, 
a 5% increase from its $14.7 million in sales in the second quarter of 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, Dolco's earnings rose 16% to $2.33 million from $2.01 
million a year before. Its sales grew 6%, to $32.5 million from $30.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Dolco attributed the improved results to increased unit volume and a change in 
its product mix to include higher-priced products. 
