<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: NORTH L. A. REGION SHOWS SLIGHT OFFICE VACANCY DROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The northern Los Angeles commercial real estate market, which includes the San 
Fernando, Santa Clarita and Conejo valleys and part of Ventura County, saw 
office vacancies decline to 16.8% in the second quarter from 16.9% in the first 
quarter, according to a survey by the brokerage Cushman & Wakefield of 
California Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 The highest vacancy rate locally was reported in the west San Fernando Valley, 
which had a 21.1% rate of empty offices in the second quarter, up from 19% in 
the first three months of the year.The central Valley, which includes the 
Valencia-Newhall area, had a 16.7% vacancy rate, up from 15.7% in the first 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 The East Valley vacancy rate continued to tighten, to 12.8% from 15.2%. 
</P>
<P>
 The Simi and Conejo valleys had a 19.1% vacancy rate in the second quarter, 
down from 19.4%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
