<P>
VOICE POWERED'S LOSS NARROWS IN SECOND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Voice Powered Technology International Inc., a Sherman Oaks-based maker of 
voice-recognition consumer electronic products, reported a narrower loss for 
its second quarter that ended June 30. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported a loss of $141,000, compared with a loss of $5.25 million 
for the same period a year earlier.Revenue for the latest quarter was $2.64 
million, down 45% from $4.81 million in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first six months of 1994, Voice Powered posted a loss of $36,000 on 
revenue of $5.76 million, compared with a year-earlier loss of $7.65 million on 
