ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CYPRESS; MEMBERS SOUGHT FOR YOUTH COMMISSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is seeking high school-age applicants for the 1994-95 Cypress Youth 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission helps the city with many functions, including the 
Adopt-a-Family Program and Youth-in-Government Day. 
</P>
<P>
 Other activities include holiday events like the Cypress Easter Egg Hunt and 
the city's Youth Art and Creative Writing Contest. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are taking applications until 5 p.m. Friday, Aug. 12," said June Liu, 
recreations services manager for the city. 
</P>
<P>
 Liu, who serves as the staff liaison for the Youth Commission, said 15 seats 
will be filled. 
</P>
<P>
 Liu said the applicants are interviewed by Recreation and Park Commission 
members, who then make recommendations to the City Council, which does the 
actual appointing.  
</P>
<P>
 Liu said applicants cannot be over 18 and must be eligible for high school. 
</P>
<P>
 "The applicants must at least be freshmen in high school this year," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applicants also must be Cypress residents, able to attend Youth Commission 
meetings on the first and third Tuesdays of each month at 6 p.m., and be 
"willing to devote the necessary time and effort to research, coordinate and 
execute commission projects." 
</P>
<P>
 Applications can be made at the Cypress Personnel Department, 5275 Orange 
Ave., by the deadline, 5 p.m. Friday. BILL BILLITER 
