HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mary Nahas, office manager at Arroyo Vista School, has been named one of five 
statewide employees of the year by the California School Employees Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Nahas, who has been at the school for two years, is scheduled to receive her 
award today at the CSEA's 68th annual conference in San Jose. 
</P>
<P>
 Nahas of Mission Viejo was selected the top office manager out of 84 nominees 
throughout the state, said Dick Campbell, principal at Arroyo Vista School. 
</P>
<P>
 "To be judged first in the state was pretty impressive," Campbell said. "We 
are very proud of her." 
</P>
<P>
 Nahas has been a member of the CSEA's Capistrano chapter since 1985. She is 
the chapter's chief job steward. 
</P>
<P>
 Before coming to Arroyo Vista School, Nahas worked at Viejo School in Mission 
Viejo for eight years. 
</P>
<P>
 Nahas started with the district in 1979 as a school clerk, said Jacqueline 
Price, spokeswoman for the Capistrano Unified School District. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
