<P>
TRUST FUND SET UP IN SEARCH FOR MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The family of a missing private security guard said Monday they are setting up 
a trust fund to aid in the search for Michael Jerome Williams, who disappeared 
July 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams' father, the Rev. Frank Williams, assistant pastor at Friendship 
Baptist Church in Long Beach, announced the formation of a family trust, part 
of which would be used as a reward for locating 32-year-old man. 
</P>
<P>
 The family also announced that it has hired a private investigator to help 
locate Williams, who was last seen leaving his Santa Ana home for Newport Beach 
to pick up his paycheck and new security guard uniform. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, Anaheim police said they stopped three teen-agers who were in a 
rental car that Williams had been using while his was being repaired. A 
juvenile driving the white 1991 Ford Taurus was detained because he was wanted 
for an outstanding warrant, police said. The others were questioned, then 
released. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams is described as African American, 5 feet 8, 170 pounds and missing 
two front teeth. Anyone with information is asked to contact Santa Ana police 
at (714) 834-4801. 
</P>
