<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: HEALTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Berkeley Firm Signs AIDS Test Deal: Calypte Biomedical, developer of a urine 
test used to detect the virus that causes AIDS, has signed a distribution deal 
with Otsuka Pharmaceutical Co. that gives the Japanese firm exclusive rights to 
market the test throughout Asia. Calypte, a research and development firm, 
valued the deal with Japan's fourth-largest drug company at more than $50 
million. The disease is spreading rapidly in Asia, and the World Health 
Organization estimates that the number of HIV-positive individuals in Asia 
could quadruple to 10 million by 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
