<P>
 Pasadena-based Tetra Tech Inc. announced that it has signed a contract with 
the U.S. Air Force Air Mobility Command to provide environmental engineering 
services. The five-year contract is valued at $100 million. . . . 
Washington-based Host Marriott Corp. said it completed the previously announced 
sale of 26 Fairfield Inns for about $115 million to a venture formed by Sage 
Hospitality Resources Inc. and Carlyle Group. . . . Mexico's Grupo Dina 
consortium has completed the purchase of Phoenix-based bus maker Motor Coach 
Industries International in a $300-million deal. 
</P>
