<P>
FOCUS ON ENTERTAINMENT STOCKS : COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Market trends: Microsoft Corp. was the volume leader in Monday's trading. 
Elsewhere, AMC Entertainment Inc., one of the largest motion picture exhibitors 
in the United States, announced first-quarter profit of $1.6 million on $128.5 
million in sales, compared to a year-earlier profit of $3.1 million on $135.9 
million in sales. The company attributed the decline in first-quarter revenue 
to "weaker film product which resulted in lower attendance levels." 
</P>
