<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEALS: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BATES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Film: Things might be coming together soon for former TriStar Chairman Mike 
Medavoy in his efforts to set up a production and distribution entity.Medavoy 
has pretty much gained the financing commitments. In a brief interview, he 
confirmed that a deal is close but that several loose ends are still being tied 
up by lawyers working on the project. Medavoy said he is getting enthusiastic 
response to his plans. He began working with former Carolco executive Peter 
Hoffman and former Columbia/TriStar International executive Arnold Messer 
shortly after he left TriStar in the wake of a falling out with the brass at 
TriSar parent Sony Pictures. JAMES BATES 
</P>
