<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOWNTIME: BODY WATCH; TRYING ON THOSE HIGH FASHION IMAGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I love to leaf through a high fashion magazine, looking at those creations 
that are far beyond my reach. I visualize myself standing in the doorway of 
some pristine resort, arm up to the archway, a slim shadow cast behind. It's 
the second best feeling in the world, not having slipped to depths of 
self-indulgence, and then having those feelings of guilt and remorse, for 
whipping myself into a frenzy of shopping for a little number that looks good 
only when worn by someone who has not eaten more than a stalk of celery in a 
lifetime. 
</P>
<P>
 -- SALLYE CARPENTER, South Pasadena 
</P>
