<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: HALIFAX; ROYALS IN CANADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Queen Elizabeth II and Prince Philip arrive in Halifax, Nova Scotia, Saturday 
for a nine-day visit to Canada. The queen, Canada's head of state, will spend 
three days in Halifax, then fly on to Victoria, British Columbia, where she 
will officially open the Commonwealth Games. 
</P>
<P>
 She is scheduled to watch some events, including swimming and gymnastics, and 
participate in a round of building and garden dedications and dinners with 
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien. Prince Philip is scheduled to tour the 
Khutzeymateen Valley in northern British Columbia. Philip, president of World 
Wildlife Fund International, has called for conservation of the valley, a home 
to grizzly bears. 
</P>
<P>
 Also on the itinerary: a brief visit to Yellowknife, in the Northwest 
Territories, before the royals depart on Aug. 21. 
</P>
