<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: SAUGERTIES; WOODSTOCK REDUX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Twenty-five years after the original concert was held on Max Yasgur's farm, 
Woodstock '94 takes place near Saugerties, N.Y., in the Hudson Valley for three 
days beginning Friday.Promoters hope the event will be not only a reunion but 
attract the sons and daughters of the Woodstock generation. More than 30 bands 
plus a six-acre, interactive multimedia "Surreal Field," aimed, according to 
Danny Socolof, its architect, at "the first postgraduates of Nintendo 
University." Promoters also hope the rain and mud that marked the original 
concert will be missing. 
</P>
