<P>
BASEBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; SANDERS CHARGED WITH 
MISDEMEANORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cincinnati Red outfielder Deion Sanders was charged with two misdemeanors 
Monday night following an altercation with a security officer at Riverfront 
Stadium.Police Lt. Fred Ramsey said off-duty Cincinnati police officer Herb 
Kohus was guarding a stadium pedestrian entrance and stopped Sanders as he 
tried to drive his motorcycle through it. Sanders was charged with failing to 
provide a driver's license and resisting arrest. The officer suffered minor 
injuries, Ramsey said. Police will interview more witnesses today and consult 
with prosecutors before deciding whether to add an assault charge. 
</P>
