<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE & DEFENSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TRW Appeals Loss of Satellite Award: The company's aerospace unit in Redondo 
Beach asked the General Accounting Office to review its recent loss of a 
top-secret military satellite contract, a source familiar with the award 
said.TRW last year had won the contract, which would have generated more than 
$2.5 billion in revenue over the next decade. But federal authorities last 
month stripped the contract from TRW and awarded it to archrival Martin 
Marietta Corp. after Martin and Lockheed Corp. protested that TRW had submitted 
a "low-ball" bid. The GAO has issued a stop-work order on the contract pending 
TRW's appeal. 
</P>
