<P>
 Canadian Company Sweetens Bid for Gold Mining Firm: Upstart Royal Oak Mines 
Inc. raised its offer for Lac Minerals Ltd. to $1.74 billion (U.S.) and 
predicted victory in the battle for the much-bigger gold mining firm. Royal Oak 
lifted its bid to $3.60 in cash plus two of its shares for each Lac share, 
valuing the target at $12 a share -- a 45% premium to Lac's market price before 
Royal Oak's first bid July 7.Separately, Lac rejected a rival offer from mining 
giant American Barrick Resource Corp. Analysts say they expect the battle for 
Lac to intensify with revised offers from rival bidders, including American 
Barrick. Barrick offered $2.90 cash plus 0.31 of its shares, or a total of 0.43 
shares, valuing Lac at $1.5 billion. 
