month's auction of licenses for interactive TV service said it will not submit 
bid deposits and will file an appeal with the Federal Communications 
Commission. Commercial Realty of St. Pete Inc. said in a statement that product 
delays by the inventor of the technology could prevent it from launching the 
service within the government-mandated time frame. The FCC had warned license 
winners that if they did not meet Monday's deadline for down payments they 
would be slapped with penalties. 
